headlines.description: — Joel Embiid and James Harden were greeted by loud roars from the plenty of Philadelphia fans that packed Madison Square Garden.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid has 37, Harden a triple-double as 76ers beat Knicks

headlines.description: — The Utah Jazz are reasonably healthy, hitting shots and reasserting themselves as a Western Conference powerhouse.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell, Gobert lead surging Jazz over Suns, 118-114

headlines.description: — Indiana Pacers coach Rick Carlisle knew his team needed to work hard for quality shots.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brissett, Pacers hot from long range, beat Celtics 128-107

headlines.description: — Kelly Olynyk made a fadeaway jumper from the baseline at the overtime buzzer and the Detroit Pistons beat Charlotte 127-126 on Sunday night, their first victory over the Hornets in nearly 4 1/2 years.
headlines.shortLinkText: Olynyk's buzzer-beater in OT ends Pistons' skid vs. Hornets

headlines.description: — Reggie Jackson scored 26 points, including three key points down the stretch to lead the Los Angeles Clippers to a 99-98 victory over the Houston Rockets on Sunday night to open a two-game series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson scores 26 points, Clippers outlast Rockets 99-98

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Outside the victorious Dallas locker room, coach Jason Kidd had a little fun with Mavericks superstar Luka Doncic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donic leads big comeback, Mavericks stun Warriors 107-101

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — JaMychal Green had 20 points and 10 rebounds off the bench and the Denver Nuggets pushed their winning streak to six games with a 124-92 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nuggets beat Blazers 124-92, extend win streak to 6 games

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — The New Orleans Pelicans are starting to find their stride since acquiring CJ McCollum nearly three weeks ago. Two nights after a surprising win at Phoenix, the Pelicans rolled to their biggest victory over the reeling Los Angeles Lakers.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum, Pelicans roll to 123-95 win over reeling Lakers
